0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","article",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__articlePage","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"Trex vs Wood Decking: Cost and Maintenance Comparison 2026\",\"image\":[\"https://www.ldndecks.com/images/img13.jpeg\"],\"datePublished\":\"2026-04-04T04:00:00.000Z\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-04-04T04:00:00.000Z\",\"author\":[{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks Team\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\"}],\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\",\"logo\":{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/ldndecks-logo.webp\"}},\"description\":\"Comparing smooth composite decking materials to rich natural wood. Which one offers the best long-term value for Northern Virginia homeowners?\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/blog/trex-vs-wood-decking\"},\"isAccessibleForFree\":true,\"inLanguage\":\"en-US\",\"speakable\":{\"@type\":\"SpeakableSpecification\",\"cssSelector\":[\".leadParagraph\",\"h1\",\"h2\"]}}"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgWrapper","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"src":"/images/img13.jpeg","alt":"Trex vs Wood Decking: Cost and Maintenance Comparison 2026","fill":true,"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroImg","priority":true,"sizes":"100vw"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgOverlay","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerLarge","children":[["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__backLink","children":"← Back to News"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__title","children":"Trex vs Wood Decking: Cost and Maintenance Comparison 2026"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__meta","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__author","children":["By ","Loudoun Decks Team"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__divider","children":"•"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"April 4, 2026"}]]}]]}]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerNarrow","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentBody","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__leadParagraph","children":"Comparing smooth composite decking materials to rich natural wood. Which one offers the best long-term value for Northern Virginia homeowners?"}],[["$","p","0",{"children":"Choosing the right decking material is the foundational decision of your backyard remodel. Homeowners frequently ask us whether the higher upfront cost of Trex composite outweighs the classic, rustic appeal and lower material cost of pressure-treated wood. The answer lies in your long-term maintenance tolerance and the intense Northern Virginia climate."}],["$","h2","1",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"The True Cost of Natural Wood"}],["$","p","2",{"children":"Pressure-treated pine, cedar, and redwood offer a beautiful, organic aesthetic that is hard to genuinely replicate. At initial installation, natural wood is significantly cheaper than composite. However, wood is biologically active. In the freezing winters and humid summers of Loudoun County, wood will naturally expand and contract. "}],["$","p","3",{"children":"To prevent splitting, warping, and serious rot, wood decks require rigorous annual maintenance. You must thoroughly power-wash, sand, and restain or seal the deck every 12 to 24 months. When you calculate the cost of professional staining over a 10-year period, the \"cheap\" wood deck rapidly becomes thousands of dollars more expensive than composite."}],"$L4","$L5","$L6","$L7","$L8","$L9"],"$La"]}]}]}],"$Lb"]}],["$Lc"],"$Ld"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"Jebrcr4Vyd2YosxlccnHN"}
4:["$","h2","4",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"The Trex Composite Advantage"}]
5:["$","p","5",{"children":"Trex and other modern composite materials (like TimberTech) provide a splinter-free, highly durable alternative. Manufactured from 95% recycled plastic film and reclaimed sawdust, these boards are engineered to resist fading, staining, and mold growth."}]
6:["$","h3","6",{"style":{"marginTop":"30px","marginBottom":"15px","color":"#222"},"children":"Zero Maintenance"}]
7:["$","p","7",{"children":"The primary selling point of composite decking is what you *don’t* have to do. You never need to buy stain, you never need to rent a floor sander, and you never have to pull a splinter out of your foot. A simple semi-annual cleaning with soap and water is all that is required to keep a Trex deck looking brand new for decades."}]
8:["$","h3","8",{"style":{"marginTop":"30px","marginBottom":"15px","color":"#222"},"children":"25-Year Warranties"}]
9:["$","p","9",{"children":"Premium composites are backed by 25 to 50-year fade and stain warranties. While the upfront investment is higher, the ROI is mathematically indisputable if you plan on staying in your home for more than 5 years. For busy Northern Virginia families, composite is the superior choice for longevity and peace of mind."}]
a:["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__conclusionBox","children":[["$","h3",null,{"children":"Ready to upgrade your outdoor living space?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Contact Loudoun Decks today for a free estimate and planning consultation."}],["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/contact","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__ctaBtn","children":"Get Started"}]]}]
